<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: IN THE GROOVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cross Michael Jackson's greatest-hits album off your Christmas wish list. The 
release has been pushed back to next year. A source at Epic Records, Jackson's 
label, says the performer has written a lot of new songs and wants to finish 
recording them all before choosing several to include in the package. There is 
a possibility that more than two or three new songs will be included in the 
multi-record set, but there are no official plans for an entire new album at 
this time. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
