<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Coast Repertory is one of seven theaters -- and one of only two outside 
of New York -- to snag a chunk of the $300,000 that will be provided for the 
production of six new plays as part of AT&amp;T's "New Plays for the '90s 
Project." The Costa Mesa theater will receive $50,000 for its staging of Howard 
Korder's "Search and Destroy," scheduled to open Jan. 12. The winning entries 
were selected from proposals submitted by 35 theaters. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
