<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARRIAGE DISASTROUS BEFORE IT EVEN STARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tom Newberry may be a candidate for the unluckiest man in America. 
</P>
<P>
The plane he was aboard Wednesday night on the way to his wedding -- USAir 
Flight 5050 -- crashed on takeoff at New York's La Guardia Airport. 
</P>
<P>
His wedding was scheduled for Saturday in Wilmington, N.C., which is in the 
path of Hurricane Hugo. 
</P>
<P>
Newberry's honeymoon was to have been in the Virgin Islands, which were 
devastated earlier this week by the hurricane and subsequently by looting and 
rioting. 
</P>
<P>
His plans now? The couple will take "a different track," he said Thursday on 
NBC's "Today" show. 
</P>
