<P>
FAIR GOT BUM STEER; GIRL FORFEITS PRIZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLUMBUS, Ohio 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-ager whose steer won grand prize at the Ohio State Fair will forfeit her 
ribbon and $28,000 following charges that the animal had been entered under 
another name in Illinois and its hide dyed to conceal the ruse. 
</P>
<P>
The Ohio Expositions Commission on Thursday approved an agreement reached with 
the family of 17-year-old Susan Shealy, whose Angus-cross steer Hank won the 
blue ribbon in August. 
</P>
