<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
AUTOPSY CONFIRMS JUDGE KILLED HIMSELF WITH GUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An autopsy Thursday confirmed that Orange County Superior Court Judge James R. 
Franks II committed suicide by firing a single gunshot into his chest, a 
Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Richard J. Olson said a preliminary autopsy showed that Franks died of one 
shot from a 9-millimeter handgun. Toxicological tests were performed, but the 
results will not be available for six to eight weeks, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
The jurist's body was discovered Wednesday in a wooded area of Trabuco Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Franks, 49, had been presiding over the triple-murder trial of Thomas 
Maniscalco in Superior Court in Santa Ana but had taken a paid sick leave 
several weeks ago. He reportedly suffered from emphysema. 
</P>
</TEXT>
