<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trading places: The presidents of Citizens Bank of Costa Mesa and El Camino 
Bank in Anaheim have switched jobs. Robert Ucciferri moved to Citizens after 
about nine months as head of El Camino, while Richard Helstrom, recently hired 
as president of Citizens, moved to El Camino. Ucciferri, who had been an 
executive at Citizens for 10 years, said he left late last year to take over at 
El Camino because he wanted to run a bank. When the president's post opened in 
July, Ucciferri asked to return. Helstrom was hired at Citizens but was willing 
to go instead to El Camino, Simpson said. Both banks are owned by Citizens 
Holdings. 
