<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSMAKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lester Hill has been named president of Symbol Technologies Inc.'s Portable 
Data Systems Division in Costa Mesa. The division, previously known as MSI Data 
until its acquisition by Symbol in November, 1988, makes portable, hand-held 
data terminals. Hill was formerly president and chief executive officer of Data 
Design Laboratories in Cucamonga. Before that, he headed TRW's Electronic 
Components Group. In his 19-year career with TRW, Hill also headed its 
Optoelectronics Division. 
</P>
<P>
Symbol Technologies, based in Bohemia, N.Y., manufactures hand-held laser 
scanners, portable data terminals and radio frequency devices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
