<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCR SNAGS $50,000 NEW PLAY GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Coast Repertory is one of seven theaters -- and one of only two outside 
of New York -- to snag a chunk of $300,000 being provided for the production of 
six new plays as part of an AT&amp;T "New Plays for the '90s" project. 
</P>
<P>
The Costa Mesa theater will receive $50,000 for its staging of Howard Korder's 
"Search and Destroy," scheduled to open Jan. 12. The winning entries were 
selected from proposals submitted by 35 theaters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
